Summarize function

Full dataset

summarise_asv_set <- function(asv_set) {

    
# Map of number of samples    
    asv_samples <- asv_set %>% 
      group_by(file_code, longitude, latitude) %>% 
      summarize(n = n()) %>% 
      group_by(longitude, latitude)%>% 
      summarize(n_samples = n()) %>% 
      ungroup()
      
    

  world <- map_data("world")

  g <- ggplot() + 
    geom_polygon(data = world, aes(x=long, y = lat, group = group), fill="grey") + 
    coord_fixed(1.3) +
    geom_point(data=asv_samples, aes(x=longitude, y=latitude, size=n_samples), fill="blue", shape=21) + 
    scale_size_area(trans="log10") +
    ggtitle("Number of samples")
  print(g)

  phyloseq_long_treemap(asv_set, 
                        division, class,
                        "Class" )
  phyloseq_long_treemap(asv_set, 
                        class, genus, "Genus" )
  
  return(asv_samples)
    
  }

Specific genus or species

summarise_asv_set_species <- function(asv_set) {

    
# Map of number of samples where genus found   
    asv_summary <- asv_set %>% 
      distinct(file_code, species, longitude, latitude, .keep_all = TRUE) %>% 
      count(species, longitude, latitude, name="n_samples") 
    
   print(knitr::kable(asv_summary))
    

  world <- map_data("world")

  g <- ggplot() + 
    geom_polygon(data = world, aes(x=long, y = lat, group = group), fill="grey") + 
    coord_fixed(1.3) +
    geom_point(data=asv_summary, aes(x=longitude, y=latitude, size=n_samples), fill="blue", shape=21) + 
    scale_size_area(trans="log10") +
    ggtitle("Number of samples where species found") +
    facet_wrap(vars(species))
  print(g)

# Number of reads per data set, substate    
    asv_summary <- asv_set %>% 
      mutate(sample_label = str_c(dataset_code,substrate, sep="-")) %>% 
      group_by(species, sample_label, longitude, latitude) %>% 
      summarize(n = sum(n_reads)) 
    
    print(knitr::kable(asv_summary))
    
  g <- ggplot(asv_summary, aes(x=sample_label, y=n)) +
     geom_col() +
     coord_flip() +
     scale_y_log10()+
     ylab("Number of reads") + 
     facet_wrap(vars(species))
     # facet_wrap(vars(species), scales="free_x") 
  print(g)
  
# Number of reads per data set, station, and substate    
    asv_summary <- asv_set %>% 
      mutate(sample_label = str_c(dataset_code,station_id, substrate, sep="-")) %>% 
      group_by(species, sample_label, longitude, latitude) %>% 
      summarize(n = sum(n_reads)) 
    
    print(knitr::kable(asv_summary))
    
  g <- ggplot(asv_summary, aes(x=sample_label, y=n)) +
     geom_col() +
     coord_flip() +
     scale_y_log10()+
     ylab("Number of reads") + 
     facet_wrap(vars(species))
     # facet_wrap(vars(species), scales="free_x") 
  print(g)
   
 # Timing per station and species  

    asv_summary <- asv_set %>% 
    # filter(dataset_id == 21) %>% 
    mutate(sample_label = str_c(dataset_code,station_id, substrate, sep="-")) %>% 
    group_by(species, dataset_id, sample_label, date) %>% 
    summarize(n = sum(n_reads))   
    
    
    
  g <- ggplot(asv_summary, aes(x=date, y=n)) +
     geom_col() +
     ylab("Number of reads")+ 
     theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 0, vjust = 0.5)) +
     facet_grid(cols= vars(species), rows = vars(dataset_id), scales="free_y" ) 
  print(g)   
  
  return(asv_summary)
   
    
  }

Filtering samples

Remove the following samples * Sorted * RNA * Experiments

Keep only * Pseudohaptolina_birgeri

# Remove the samples not wanted
  asv_all <- asv_set_all$df %>% 
    # filter(is.na(experiment_name)) %>%  
    # filter(is.na(sample_sorted)) %>% 
    filter(DNA_RNA == "DNA") 



 samples <-  asv_all %>% 
   group_by (file_code, dataset_id, dataset_name, substrate, fraction_name, 
             date, depth, region, station_id, latitude, longitude) %>% 
   summarize(n_reads_total = sum(n_reads)) %>% 
   ungroup()

  asv_species <- asv_all %>% 
    filter(species == "Pseudohaptolina_birgeri") %>% 
    group_by(file_code) %>% 
    summarise(n_reads_species = sum(n_reads)) %>% 
    ungroup()
  
  asv_species <- left_join(samples, asv_species) %>% 
    mutate(n_reads_species =  replace_na(n_reads_species, 0))
Joining, by = "file_code"
  openxlsx::write.xlsx(asv_species, "Pseudohaptolina_birgeri.xlsx", zoom=80, firstRow=TRUE, colWidths="auto")

g_map_polar

##Using sf

  • Must transform data frame to sf object (if not coordinates are not correctly transformed)
  • Cannot use jitter
  • In polar coordinates, the limits are a bit tricky to determine (must transform lat long to polar)
  world <- rnaturalearth::ne_countries(scale = "medium", returnclass = "sf")
  
  proj_longlat <- "+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +no_defs +ellps=WGS84 +towgs84=0,0,0"
  proj_polar <-"+proj=laea +lat_0=75 +lon_0=20 "

  asv_species_present <- asv_species %>% 
    filter(n_reads_species > 0) %>% 
    select(substrate, latitude, longitude) %>% 
    mutate(substrate = str_replace(substrate, "first year ", "")) %>% 
    distinct() %>% 
    sf::st_as_sf( coords = c("longitude", "latitude"),
                  crs = proj_longlat) 

  asv_species_absent <- asv_species %>% 
    filter(n_reads_species == 0) %>% 
    select(substrate, latitude, longitude) %>% 
    distinct() %>% 
    sf::st_as_sf( coords = c("longitude", "latitude"),
                  crs = proj_longlat)
  
  

  g_map_sf <- ggplot() + 
    geom_sf(data = world, color="grey", fill="grey")+
    xlab("Longitude") + ylab("Latitude") +
    geom_sf (data=asv_species_absent,color="grey40", shape=3, size=1) +
    geom_sf(data=asv_species_present,
               aes(fill=substrate, color=substrate), 
               shape=21, size=2) +
    coord_sf(expand = FALSE) +
    theme_light() +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = (-2:2) * 90) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = (-2:2) * 30)  +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("green","red", "blue"))+
    scale_color_manual(values = c("green","red", "blue")) +
    theme(plot.tag = element_text(size= 20)) +
    labs(tag="A")
                 
  print(g_map_sf)

  xmin <- sf::sf_project(from=proj_longlat, to=proj_polar, matrix(c(-90,60),ncol=2))
  xmin <- xmin[,1]
  xmax <- sf::sf_project(from=proj_longlat, to=proj_polar, matrix(c(+90,60),ncol=2))
  xmax <- xmax[,1]
  ymin <- sf::sf_project(from=proj_longlat, to=proj_polar, matrix(c(0,60),ncol=2))
  ymin <- ymin[,2]
  ymax <- sf::sf_project(from=proj_longlat, to=proj_polar, matrix(c(180,60),ncol=2))
  ymax <- ymax[,2]

  g_map_polar_sf <- ggplot() +

sanitize.italics <- function(str) {
  str_replace_all(str, c("_" = "\\\\_", 
                         "\\{" = "\\\\textit{", 
                         "Ã‚Â°" = "\\\\degree",
                         "X" = "\\\\cellcolor{gray}"))
}

Table of datasets (Table S1)

# table <- readxl::read_excel(path="metapr2_datasets.xlsx")

  asv_species_present <- asv_species %>% 
    filter(n_reads_species > 0) %>%
    group_by(dataset_id, substrate) %>% 
    summarise(n_reads_species_total = sum(n_reads_species)) %>%
    group_by(dataset_id) %>% 
    summarise(n_reads_species_total = sum(n_reads_species_total),
           substrate = str_c(substrate, collapse = ", ")) 

table <- datasets_selected %>% 
  left_join(asv_species_present) %>% 
  arrange(gene_region, region, dataset_id) %>%
  mutate(bioproject_accession = case_when (is.na(bioproject_accession) ~ web_link,
                                           TRUE ~ bioproject_accession)) %>% 
  select(ID = dataset_id,
         `Gene region` = gene_region,
         Description = dataset_name, 
         `Oceanic region` = region,
         `Bioproject or Repository` = bioproject_accession,
         `DOI paper` = doi,
         `Reads #` = n_reads_species_total,
         `Substrate` = substrate)


table_tex <- xtable::xtable(table, label="tablesup:metabarcodes", 
                        caption='Datasets considered for metabarcode analysis. These datasets correspond to the V4 and V9 region of the 18S rRNA gene.  All datasets have been processed with the dada2 software \\citep{Callahan2016} to extract ASV (amplicon single variants).', 
                        align = c("l", "c", "c", "l", "l", "l", "l", "l", "l"),
                        digits=0)
print(table_tex,  scalebox = 0.5, 
      caption.placement = "top",
      include.rownames = FALSE, 
      file="table_metabarcodes.tex",
      sanitize.text.function = sanitize.italics)
